The accident, which killed a twenty-two-year-old stewardess last week, was probably caused by the driver of the truck crossing the bus.
The young woman was sitting at that moment, to all the misfortune, next to the driver, in the least safe place in the car, although she had two more places available.
However, a bus can also have an accident or brake sharply when the steward carries coffee or newspapers.
It also plays a role whether the bus is equipped with parking spaces according to the vehicle letter.
If this is not provided in the bus, the passengers must sit.
Student Agency’s long-distance buses have no parking spaces; this was confirmed by the company’s director, Radim Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura, to Aktualj.cz.
"We discussed this with the ministry, and this did not initially agree with the movement of travelers.
Later this was withdrawn, and we reached a consensus that travelers may go to the toilet during the ride if they have their seat,” he said.
The law does not know a steward.
“There is no clear legal interpretation for the role of a steward – no legal regulation describes that role.
However, there is also no legislation prohibiting the carrier from providing services.
The law on road traffic only knows the term vehicle companions; however, its rights and obligations do not define it," adds the spokesman of the Ministry Hanzelka clearly.
Josef Pokorn<0xC3><0xBD>, director of the Department of Road Vehicles of the Ministry of Transport, on the other hand, believes that the law subsequently covers this issue.
"It depends on whether the bus also has parking spaces in the product approval.
