Buses are divided into city buses, where there are parking spaces and the maximum speed is limited, public transport buses with parking spaces and a higher allowed speed, and long-distance buses without parking spaces with the highest allowed speed and seats equipped with seat belts.
As in the plane, says the expert
BESIP traffic safety expert Jaroslav Ho<0xC5><0x99><0xC3><0xAD>n sees no fundamental problem in the movement of stewards on board a bus.
