The driver of the bus tried to escape by a sharp maneuver, but collided with the right front with the truck.
Jan<0xC4><0x8D>ura disputes that the two seats had been sold to the stewards.
"These places cannot be reserved for long-distance connections, they are blocked."
The company wants to sue truck drivers.
With compensation for the young woman’s family, the agency will not wait for the court judgment, but it expects financial compensation from the culprit.
A law change?
Not in sight
A more precise regulation of the movement of stewards on board a bus could bring about a statutory regulation on which a thirty-member team of experts from the Ministry of Transport has been working for over a year.
