Talking in sleep
Some children speak at night
I do not mean those who wake up and tell us something that happened the day before, but the children who talk during sleep.
When it happens to you for the first time, at best you will be frightened, but in reality it doesn’t matter.
This is a positive sleep disorder called speaking in sleep.
It is quite common, especially among children and adolescents.
Surely, more than one of you has been told that you spoke at night.
This phenomenon can occur occasionally (once in life, for example, during high fever), or regularly (every day, once a week, once a month), the next day the child can remember nothing.
There is not a single reason that causes this phenomenon.
Often, associations with other phenomena in sleep are sought, such as nightmares, panic fear at night, enuresis noctura (wetting at night), talking in sleep, but there is no reason for this.
As we mentioned earlier, it can be due to very high fiber, stressful situations or overwork.
In any case, this is a little researched phenomenon.
The frequency with which it occurs is very variable.
It can be that one speaks quietly in single words, whispers or it can be quite the opposite (cries, crying, long discussions ).
In cases where the utterance is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and consult with a specialist to check if there is a problem that causes anxiety and occurs in this way.
We have said that it is a positive disorder, so it is not treated, whether it is associated with another sleep disorder that can be treated (for example, with sleep apnea or with stress).
What you can do is to carry out a series of simple preventive measures:
Try not to excite the child before going to sleep.
So, choose a quiet game for the child and avoid stressful TV shows that are terrible and a bit too wild.
In the nervous children who are recommended to relax, relaxation methods can be used to help them get some inner peace.
This helps the child to sleep calmly.
When talking occurs once in sleep, try to keep the calm.
Remember that it is harmless to the child and the next day he will not be able to remember anything that happened.
Helpful advices
Don't wake it.
This is useless, because the child is unconscious, so you will tear it out of sleep.
Although the child speaks, he sleeps, so he rests.
Remember, if after a couple of appearances it turns out to be frightened, then it is recommended to consult or find out why the child is afraid.
If they understand what it says (which is not so common), the child does not put pressure on them to conduct an interrogation and get more information.
So you will not be able to achieve anything with it, because when the child sleeps, it is unconscious and can not think about it.
Also, you will hear what it says, but you will not know what it is dreaming and why it is saying, so be careful with the interpretation of the information and the conclusions you draw from it.
Perhaps, it does not tell the child that you hear it at night and know its secrets.
Not even as a joke.
This causes a lot of fear.
So don’t worry, it’s not a bad thing, it’s a moment that only takes a few minutes.
